{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/3031", "repo": "rails", "body": "I am still not a massive fan of specifying it via `attr_accessor`. I think in an ideal world we'd use an options hash, e.g.\r\n\r\n``` ruby\r\nActiveSupport::MessageVerifier.new(\r\n  \"Hey, I'm a secret!\",\r\n  :serializer => JSONSerializer,\r\n  :cipher     => 'bcrypt'\r\n)\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt would be possible to implement this with a deprecation for if the second argument is not a hash. What do you guys think?", "_id": {"$oid": "52383bd5bd3543c15101033a"}, "issue_id": 3031, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/2107028", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/3031#issuecomment-2107028", "updated_at": "2011-09-15T17:48:18Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton", "login": "jonleighton", "gravatar_id": "2940bc7d4506f3e099e3dcc32a412b98", "html_url": "https://github.com/jonleighton", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/2940bc7d4506f3e099e3dcc32a412b98?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F798cebccb32617ad94123450fd137104.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 1979, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2011-09-15T17:48:18Z", "id": 2107028, "owner": "rails"}
